The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, June 26, 2004 				 Saarc to bridge digital gap 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 25: India is set to take the lead in the adoption of a new plan of action on telecommunications for South Asian Association for Regional Co-operation (Saarc) countries.																								The move will help set up inter-country links, an intra-regional high bandwidth hub, promote research and development activities and exchange of expertise in telecommunication disciplines.																								The action plan will also stress on complete digitalisation of inter-country links. It will ensure universal access, development of rural services and affordable tariffs of telecommunication services.																								Union minister of communications and information technology, Dayanidhi Maran will lead a high-level delegation to the second meeting of Saarc communications ministers, scheduled to be held on Tuesday and Wednesday at Islamabad.																								Telecom Commission chairman Nripendra Misra will accompany the minister along with other senior officials of the department of telecommunications. During the two-day meeting, Maran will discuss various issues concerning the region, including the issue of bridging the digital divide in South Asia. 
